    "Section 6 discusses challenges and recommendations in the area.",
    "Finally, Sect. 7 gathers concluding remarks.",
    "Digital forgetting refers to procedures used to remove information from software systems.",
    "This term originated from privacy laws related to the right of erasure or the right to be forgotten (e.g.",
    "17, (European Parliament and Council of the European Union, 2016)), which enables data subjects to request service providers to delete information related to them from their systems."
